Tit. 3. 2 supa), Justinian points out three more specific significations which it bears (specialiter alias.. . . alias .. . . alias), viz. (1) ὕβρις or contumelia, the sense in which it is used in this Title; (a) culpa or ἀδίκημα, as where one speaks of damnum iniuria datum under the lex Aquilia5 and (3) ἀδικία or injustice, sensu stricto, in one whose fonction it is ‘ius pronuntiare,’ such as a judge ora magistrate.
